newsitem.title: INDONESIA: Indonesia late rubber unchanged, trade dull.
newsitem.headline: Indonesia late rubber unchanged, trade dull.

text.p: Indonesian rubber prices were stable in late trading on Wednesday after easing in the early session amid thin buying interest, dealers said.

They said January tyre-grade SIR20 offer prices eased 0.25 cents to 56.00 cents/lb in Medan. It was on offer at 55.50- 55.75 cents fob Palembang, Padang and Surabaya and at 55.125 cents fob Jambi and 55.00 cents fob Pontianak.
"There was an enquiry from a Japanese tyre-maker for February shipment but no deal has been done yet," one Medan dealer said. "There's a good chance it will be done."
Another said buyers were putting pressure on prices by staying out of the market. "They are not even putting in bids, choosing to buy when they feel the price is right," he said.
Dealers said wet latex was quoted at 2,200-2,300 rupiah/kg. December RSS1 was quoted at around 128/kg fob Medan.
